                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.113/137: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Straus</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-10T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 10, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 10—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>366. Embassy’s 343, July 27, noon. The decree promised appeared in the <hi
                        rend="italic">Journal Officiel</hi> of this morning’s date. In checking over
                    the list it appears that complete rectification has been accorded in all except
                    two minor items in chemical group. Attention appropriate authorities is being
                    called to these omissions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
